          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A THIN TARGET WAS PRODUCED BY PRESSING A HOMOGENEOUS",
                " MIXTURE OF 10 MG OF LA2O3 AND 10 MG OF DEUTERIZED PO-",
                " LYETHYLENE INTO A TABLET OF 17.7 MG/CM2 (7.3 MG/CM2 OF",
                " LA). THE NATURAL ABUNDANCIES AND THERMAL CAPTURE CROSS",
                " SECTIONS WERE 0.09 PERCENT AND 57.2+/-5.7 B FOR LA-138",
                " AND 99.91 PERCENT AND 8.93+/-0.04 B FOR LA-139, RES-",
                " PECTIVELY. THE TARGET WAS SUSPENDED AT AN ANGLE OF 30",
                " DEGREES TO THE AXIS OF THE VERTICAL NEUTRON BEAM WITH-",
                " IN THE NEUTRON SHIELDING TUBE."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 1.4 CM3 HPGE DETECTOR WAS USED TO DETECT THE",
                " CAPTURE GAMMA-RAYS. THE DETECTOR WAS ENERGY-CALIBRATED",
                " USING KNOWN GAMMA-RAY ENERGIES FROM CO-57, EU-152 AND",
                " AM-241."
              ]
            }
          ],
